The paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also involves computation and function evaluation, which could fall under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The use of correlated sources and distortion measures suggests a connection to the cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the study of network configurations and transmission of information, which could be relevant to the cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category.
